<Author>HonestReviewForU
<Content>Very Good Experience This was my first time at a Candlewood Suites and it is pretty much Holiday Inn's answer to Marriott's Towne Place. If you like one, you'll probably like the other.As noted, there's no daily maid service (gee, just like home), but there were more than enough towels for three nights. And you can swap them out at the desk if you need replacements.I was upgraded (Priority Club) to a suite with a bedroom which was nice. The suite is large enough, with TVs in both rooms and a DVD/VCR combo in the living room. I borrowed a free movie from the front desk. Bed was comfy. The room also has a full-size refrigerator/freezer, very handy. Unlike Marriott, they don't offer free breakfast here, but you have a coffee maker, microwave and range top, along with a full set of dishes/silverware and a dishwasher.Check-in and out was easy. Everyone was friendly, and they graciously let me stay a bit later so that my computer wouldn't melt in the car (the Internet, by the way, is wired and very good).The location is on the side of I-17, but it was quiet. Didn't use the pool, but it looked clean. Free washing machines were handy, with mini detergent boxes available for purchase. I left before the Wed. night pizza party, but it sounded nice.One thing -- they have one of those sensors that knows when you leave and hikes the room temperature to 77. Yes, it's the wave of the future, and yes, they have to save electricity. But when it's 112 outside, it takes longer than the promised 15 minutes to returned to the desired 70.Still, overall, this is a very good choice and I'd go back. 
