<Author>Zaphod
<Content>Good business stay This was a great hotel for a four night business stay. The staff were friendly and helpful. I was upgraded to a one-bedroom suite without asking. Housekeeping is not offered on a daily basis, but for a short stay, who really needs it? The room was stocked with plenty of towels, and more were available at the front desk, if needed. The kitchen was handy, especially the full size refrigerator. The selection in The Cupboard was suprisingly good. The bed and all of the other furniture were comfortable and in great condition. There is a movie lending library at the front desk. Pappadeaux Seafood Restaurant, two doors down, is fantastic, but is the only restaurant within easy walking distance. There are many dining options at the Metro Center Mall. The complimentary Wednesday night barbeque at the hotel was a nice touch. 
